articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's cyberspace regulator on Wednesday released the first batch of mobile app stores that have completed filing business details to regulators as it enforces a new set of rules to expand oversight on mobile apps.
articles.title: China enforces new filing rules on smartphone app stores

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Britain has given the go-ahead for Equinor (EQNR.OL) to develop the Rosebank oil and gas field in the North Sea in a move likely to provoke fresh criticism from environmental campaigners.
articles.title: Britain gives green light to Rosebank oil and gas field

articles.author: Byron Kaye
articles.description: Elon Musk's X, formerly called Twitter, disabled a feature that let users report misinformation about elections, a research organisation said on Wednesday, throwing fresh concern about false claims spreading just before major U.S. and Australian votes.
articles.title: Musk's X disabled feature for reporting electoral misinformation - researcher

articles.author: Lewis Krauskopf, David Randall, Carolina Mandl
articles.description: As the Federal Reserve’s hawkish stance boosts Treasury yields and slams stocks, some investors are preparing for more pain ahead.
articles.title: Analysis: Harsh reality of 'higher-for-longer' rates looms over US stocks

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: London's embattled office market is in 'rental recession' as volumes of empty space across the capital's West End, City and Canary Wharf business districts hit a 30-year high, analysts at Jefferies said on Wednesday.
articles.title: London office market in 'rental recession' as vacancies hit 30-yr high - Jefferies

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: H&M (HMb.ST) said unusually hot weather in many of its European markets had delayed the start of the autumn shopping season, sending sales lower in September, while cost cuts helped the fashion retailer's quarterly profit rise.
articles.title: H&M blames warm weather for September sales slide

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The chairman of Australia's Qantas Airways (QAN.AX) on Wednesday vowed to stay in his role despite a host of scandals engulfing the airline, saying its biggest shareholders wanted leadership continuity even as its shares track a one-year low.
articles.title: Australia's Qantas chairman says shareholders want him despite turmoil

articles.author: Felix Light
articles.description: Tens of thousands of ethnic Armenians rushed on Wednesday to flee the breakaway region of Nagorno-Karabakh for Armenia after a lightning military operation by Azerbaijan that has recast the contours of the post-Soviet South Caucasus.
articles.title: Tens of thousands of ethnic Armenians rush to flee Nagorno-Karabakh

articles.author: David Morgan, Richard Cowan, Moira Warburton
articles.description: The U.S. Senate on Tuesday was set to try to move forward on a bipartisan bill meant to stop the government from shutting down in just five days, while the House sought to push ahead with a conflicting measure backed only by Republicans.
articles.title: Dueling US Senate, House views on funding raise likelihood of government shutdown

articles.author: Lewis Jackson
articles.description: PwC Australia gave multiple clients confidential information leaked from Australian government tax briefings, the company said on Wednesday, the first admission that clients other than Google received leaked government tax plans.
articles.title: PwC Australia gave clients other than Google confidential tax info
